modules.description: This module implements a fuzzy search index for efficiently storing and retrieving key-value pairs where keys are strings. It supports adding, removing, and querying entries with approximate string matching, returning results lazily or as lists. Use it to build auto-complete features, typo-tolerant lookups, or in-memory search engines over labeled data.

This module implements edit distance calculations and automata for approximate string matching. It works with custom string and character types provided by the `Str` module, supporting operations like building automata from strings or lists, matching strings against automata, and debugging automaton structures. Concrete use cases include implementing fuzzy search, typo correction, and auto-complete features with configurable tolerance for character-level differences.

This module implements a fuzzy search index for efficiently storing and retrieving values associated with strings. It supports adding or removing string-value pairs, exact and fuzzy lookups with a configurable match limit, and conversions to and from lists and sequences. Typical use cases include auto-complete suggestions, typo-tolerant search, and managing dynamic collections of labeled resources.

This module implements Levenshtein distance calculations and automata for approximate string matching, supporting custom string and character types. It provides functions to build automata with a specified edit distance limit, match strings against those automata, and perform efficient fuzzy searches over indexed string-value pairs. Concrete use cases include fuzzy auto-complete, typo correction, and approximate string retrieval with on-demand result evaluation.
